cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL. 

The paper proposes methods for achieving rotation and flip invariance in convolutional neural networks for image segmentation tasks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also focuses on improving the efficiency of the network, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of kernel rotation and flip also involves mathematical operations, which could place the paper in cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper involves image segmentation, which could also place it in cs.CL (Computation and Language).
